1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Codex hits the same deployment mistake in two different sessions. Each time, we add another rule, skill, or tool.
The environment grows. The friction returns.

2
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Most agent improvement systems are built for addition. Codex Metabolism asks what earns the right to remain.
Like slime mold, it explores candidate paths; later use brightens the path that works, while unsupported branches fade.

3
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:45,000
This is not a self-improving model. It is a human-approved lifecycle around Codex: synthetic sessions expose friction,
and later sessions decide whether the fix is kept, repaired, or archived.

4
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:59,000
Failure, explicit correction, and same-command recovery repeat across two sessions.
One zero-install review stages four decisions and changes nothing live.

5
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Before creating anything, it checks necessity, Codex built-ins, installed capabilities, repository assets,
and reviewed open source. If an existing path works, creation is blocked.

6
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:28,000
For this friction, the smallest reliable fix is mechanical: require the exact reviewed preflight-and-deploy sequence.
Spoofs are denied. A person reviews the evidence and diff before activation.

7
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:43,000
Two later sessions succeed. The next review returns KEEP HARNESS, VALIDATED,
and suppresses the duplicate proposal, so the same fix does not accumulate again.

8
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Other interventions do not get a free pass. Useful skills stay; an unused skill becomes only a retirement candidate.
Archive and restore remain human decisions. Nothing is silently deleted.

9
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Across twenty-seven synthetic cases: zero false positives and fifty percent recall.
This is a boundary test—not proof of magical learning or real-world impact.

10
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:32,000
We built and tested the system with Codex and GPT-5.6. In an optional synthetic run, model gpt-5.6-sol agreed on CREATE HARNESS,
challenged PATCH RULE with KEEP RULE, but deterministic gates and human approval remain authoritative.

11
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Most tools help agents remember more.
Codex Metabolism helps decide what deserves to remain.
